Do you want to add a touch of magic to your garden or house? Of course, you do! Why not make a fairy door? This easy project is great for preschoolers and easy to make. First, gather all the materials you’ll need for your fairy door. You’ll need: Once you’ve got all your materials, it’s time to get creative! To give your fairy door that extra special touch, glue a button onto the lolly stick door as a door handle, and paint a little keyhole beneath it. Let it dry, and your fairy door is complete! Now it’s time to find the perfect spot for your fairy door! It can be added to a tree, fence, or wall in the garden or stuck onto your child’s bedroom skirting board. Just make sure to place it in a dry area, as this fairy door isn’t waterproof. Watch the full video tutorial from PPLDTV below:   